        "description": "I was surprised to find you can't use standard arithmetic operators on PyArrow arrays and scalars. Instead, one must use the compute functions:\r\n\r\n{code:Python}\r\nimport pyarrow as pa\r\n\r\narr = pa.array([1, 2, 3])\r\npc.add(arr, 2)\r\n# Doesn't work:\r\n# arr + 2\r\n# arr + pa.scalar(2)\r\n# arr + arr\r\n\r\npc.multiply(arr, 20)\r\n# Doesn't work:\r\n# 20 * arr\r\n# pa.scalar(20) * arr\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nIs it intentional we don't support this?",
